				<td colspan="2"><span>im sorry if this is the wrong place to put this, but i have a big problem with everquest.
<br />

<br />
i keep changing my mind when it comes to the class choice. 
<br />

<br />
i have been almost every class at least once, and i don't know what to stick to.
<br />

<br />
i was a small time bard on Drinal, and a rather enjoyed it. since then, the bard class has been near the top of my list.
<br />

<br />
but as a necromancer, i must admit, i loved cackling at an opponent dieing from the inside out. my strongest characters on all the servers ive been to are necros. but i dont feel the enjoyment of being one as much since i started tapping into other classes.
<br />

<br />
my first characer ever was a shadow knight, and though i wasnt a strong one, i enjoyed it.
<br />

<br />
Rogues and wizards were fun as well, but i didnt play them as much as necros, bards and Shadow knights,
<br />

<br />
 well, what i want to know is, whats your opinion of some of the other classes in everquest? and, if youve been one, how did you enjoy it? I moved to Veeshan now, so i can start anew...(i generally solo, because i dont look for groups)</span></td>
