				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: highly indecisive- i need opinions.<a name="55345"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 5 04 10:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, if you don't feel like grouping, then rogue, is definitely out, they can't solo.  For that matter, no true melee is likely what I'm hearing from you, despite your SK experience.  They aren't exceptional soloers unless it's low blue to light blue (sure if they're twinked and well played, but he said he was iffy on the SK).  
<br />

<br />
I've played both a necro and a bard, though I got bored with the necro and have yet to do so with the bard.  Necros and BSTs are awesome soloers, and they do provide a less hectic solo time than a bard does (kiting is hectic IMHO).  Then again, bards are THE most versitile class in the game (read jack of all trades).  My preference is always a bard, you can do just about anything.  Necros can solo forever, but they get boring IMHO, thus the retired necro in my bank.
<br />

<br />
That's my opinion.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
