				<td colspan="2"><span>I would suggest you spend some time on Test server.
<br />

<br />
Create a toon of the above noted solo classes and give them a go. Once your in game type /testbuff and you will be set to lvl 25 with all your spells(up to that lvl) and a full suit of equipment and weapons. Go to LOIO, Maru Seru, south karana, Dalnir, etc and try out soloing stuff in those zones to see how you like it.
<br />

<br />
You can't really make any informed decisions based on what people tell you, have to experience it yourself and testserver is a great way to do it.
<br />

<br />
I'd give necro/magician/beastlord/enchanter a go first though, bards end up more social than solo players, sure we're good at it but as a bard, I enjoy the grouping aspect much more than mindless killing. With the others, solo killing is much more involved and each kill is more satisfying, keeping the level of boredom to a minimum. Not to mention, the upgrades if your going at it with no twinking come from mobs a bard would have a hard time solo.(Imagine doing Phini solo in fine steel!)
<br />

<br />
Oh, and tutuboy, I think the M your looking for is the second one :rolleyes: (try to be a little constructive, regardless of how you feel about another person's play style). </span></td>
