				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: highly indecisive- i need opinions.<a name="55467"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 04 1:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You made the right decision with the beastlord, but then I'm also very biased as mine is my main.
<br />

<br />
Seriously though, even if you end up not liking your bst, just keep trying other classes. I was like you in the first couple of years playing EQ, trying a variety of classes. Eventually my beastlord &quot;stuck&quot; with me enough. Don't continue playing classes that you don't enjoy, but do look at spell listings/skills to see how they improve later in life as this was a great motivation for me to level up. Eventually you may feel like going back to one of your alts and find them more fun than you did the first time so don't discount those either.
<br />

<br />
I'm still trying new class combos. Right now I'm two-boxing my lil berserker/druid combo more than doing anything on my other characters. I've also just started a good old fashioned warrior/cleric combo (both gnomes).
<br />

<br />
Keep hopping around until you find a class you love. It IS out there. Your bst has got as good a chance at being that class as any imo.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
