				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: highly indecisive- i need opinions.<a name="56116"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 11 04 1:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I started my bard when I first began playing.  An experienced friend suggested I start out with a bard as they did a bit of everything and I could change later.  Bad idea!  I have tried and tried to start other chars. but always end up favoring the Bard.
<br />

<br />
I had a friend quit the game and I adopted his account that had quite a bit of 60 plus chars. Druid, Cleric, Barbie, Shaman, Warrior, Rogue, Nec, and Mage.  I played around with all of them and ended up still favoring the Bard.  It could be that I am ruined by playing a bard first as I can't get used to standing still and casting and not having Selos stinks.  I gotta admit though I have also grown tired of the bard and it does take more concentration than the others (IMHO).
<br />

<br />
Each char has its own pros and cons.  At times I want to be a buff machine so I play the druid and go buff newbies.  Other times I want to sit and chat and be sure to find a group so I play the Cleric. Etc.
<br />

<br />
The bard does great in a group when played correctly and fills in what is needed along with complimenting what is there.  Solo the bard is awesome and there has been many a time that my group got wiped and I switched to swarm mode and took the foul beast alone, this is very impressive to a group by the way<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> .  Yet as a soloer I grew real tired of running in circles all day. 
<br />

<br />
Also throughout the life of the bard your necessity changes instead of always staying the same like the warrior as meat sheild or cleric as healer or chanter as CC, the bard changes.  In the begining you may be a buffer or mana singer then you move on to crowd control and soloing.  In the later levels you are the puller/scout.  All the while changing from moment to moment to everything inbetween.  I am unsure about how other chars change but I do know the bard is not a dull character or class. I have filled in as healer, tank, CC, puller, haster, slower, etc. I have to admit when looking for a group it is nice to be able to say I can do that instead of saying well they need a slower and I'm a tank or They need CC and I'm not a chanter or you can hang back with a group that is gonna snare and dot/chant and so on. It does suck at times that you are not as good as another class in most things but I believe the versatility makes up for it. Just my two cps worth.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
